item.description:
In most of the modern Linux distributions, Libre Office is available and it can be used to convert XLS or XLSX file(s) to CSV file(s) in bash.
For XLS file(s):
for i in *.xls; do libreoffice --headless --convert-to csv &#34;$i&#34;; done For XLSX file(s):
for i in *.xlsx; do libreoffice --headless --convert-to csv &#34;$i&#34;; done You may get following warning but it still works fine:
javaldx: Could not find a Java Runtime Environment!
